Java program to implement ByteArray InoutStream:

The ByteArrayInputStream class of the java.io package can be used to read an array of input data (in bytes).

It extends the InputStream abstract class.

Explanation:

I have imported sub packages io, util from the java package.
I have created a class named ByteStreamStream.
I have defined main method to begin the execution.
I have created a Scanner class to take input from the user.
I am asking the user to enter a string.
finally, I am converting the input string into byte array by using getBytes()
and I am displaying it.

TEST CASE 1:

Enter some string
balaji
Converting input string into byte array by using getBytes()
balaji
BALAJI


Enter some string
Aadarsh
Converting input string into byte array by using getBytes()
Aadarsh
AADARSh

Enter some string
pAvAn
Converting input string into byte array by using getBytes()
pAvAn
PAVAN

TEST CASE 2 :
Enter some string
63362
Converting input string into byte array by using getBytes()
63362
63362

TEST CASE 3 :
Enter some string
@32bs%
Converting input string into byte array by using getBytes()
@32bs%
@32BS%
